tafsir[2]{c,v,t}:
  72,4,"(And that the foolish one among us) i.e. the devil (used to speak concerning Allah an atrocious lie."
  72,9,"(And we used to sit on places (high) therein) in heaven (to listen) before the advent of Muhammad (pbuh). (But he who listened now) after the advent of Muhammad (pbuh) (findeth a flame) a shining star (in wait for him) from the angels in order to prevent them from listening;"